Package: fly
Type: Package
Title: Intuitive Iteration with For-Loop Syntax
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: person("Rupert", "Overall", email = "rtrack@rupertoverall.net", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides the fly() function that combines the power of lapply() with 
    the intuitive syntax of for-loops. Supports iteration over lists, vectors, 
    matrices, and data frames with optional parallel processing. Always returns 
    consistent list output while preserving names from the original collection.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    parallel
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/rupertoverall/fly
BugReports: https://github.com/rupertoverall/fly/issues
